Performance Monitoring
=============================
            ::> Node run -node <node name> -command sysstat -x -m

This command verifies the CPU usage.

Also, we need to verify that the Disk usage is more than 90%, and we get performance issues.



Cluster and Node Management
===========================
1. Check cluster and node status:
            ::> cluster show
            ::>  node show

2. Check node details:		
            ::> node show -instance
3. Check cluster health:	
            ::> system health status show
4. Display cluster uptime:	
            ::> node run -node <node_name> uptime

Storage and Aggregate Management:
==================================
5. Show aggregate status and details:

            ::> aggr show
            ::> aggr show-space
            ::> aggr show -instance

6. Create a new aggregate:

            ::> aggr create -aggregate <aggregate_name> -diskcount <number_of_disks>

7. Add disks to an aggregate:

            ::> aggr add-disks -aggregate <aggregate_name> -diskcount <number_of_disks>

8. Check disk status:

            ::> storage disk show

Volume Management:
========================
9. Show volume status and details:

            ::> vol show
            ::> vol show -instance

10. Create a new volume:

            ::> vol create -vserver <vserver_name> -volume <volume_name> -aggregate <aggregate_name> -size <size>

11. Resize a volume:

            ::> vol size <volume_name> <new_size>

12. Delete a volume:

            ::> vol delete -vserver <vserver_name> -volume <volume_name>

13. Bring a volume online or offline:

            ::> vol online <volume_name>
            ::> vol offline <volume_name>

LUN Management
==============================

14. Show LUN status and details:
            ::> lun show
            ::> lun show -vserver <vserver_name>

15. Create a new LUN:
            ::> lun create -vserver <vserver_name> -path /vol/<volume_name>/<lun_name> -size <size> -ostype <os_type>
  
16. Map a LUN to an initiator group:
            ::> lun map -vserver <vserver_name> -path /vol/<volume_name>/<lun_name> -igroup <igroup_name>

17. Unmap a LUN:
            ::> lun unmap -vserver <vserver_name> -path /vol/<volume_name>/<lun_name> -igroup <igroup_name>


Snapshot Management
==============================
18. Create a Snapshot copy:
            ::> snapshot create -volume <volume_name> -snapshot <snapshot_name>

19. Show Snapshot copies:
            ::> snapshot show -volume <volume_name>

20. Delete a Snapshot copy:
            ::> snapshot delete -volume <volume_name> -snapshot <snapshot_name>


SnapMirror Management
===============================
21. Show SnapMirror relationships:
            ::> snapmirror show

22. Create a SnapMirror relationship:
            ::> snapmirror create -source-path <source_vserver>:<source_volume> -destination-path <dest_vserver>:<dest_volume> -type DP

23. Initialize SnapMirror:
            ::> snapmirror initialize -destination-path <dest_vserver>:<dest_volume>

24. Update SnapMirror:
            ::> snapmirror update -destination-path <dest_vserver>:<dest_volume>


Network Management
=============================
25. Show network interfaces:
            ::> network interface show

26. Create a new network interface:
            ::> network interface create -vserver <vserver_name> -lif <lif_name> -role data -data-protocol <protocol> -home-node <node_name> -home-port <port>

27. Show network ports:
            ::> network port show


Security and Access Management
==============================
28. Show CIFS shares:
            ::> vserver cifs share show

29. Create a new CIFS share:
            ::> vserver cifs share create -vserver <vserver_name> -share-name <share_name> -path /<path>

30. Show NFS exports:
            ::> exportpolicy rule show

31. Create a new NFS export rule:
            ::> exportpolicy rule create -vserver <vserver_name> -policyname <policy_name> -clientmatch <client_IP> -rorule <read_rule> -rwrule <write_rule> -superuser <superuser_rule>


Performance Monitoring
==========================
32. Check system performance:
            ::> sysstat -x 1

33. Display I/O statistics:
            ::> statit

34. Monitor network performance:
            ::> netstat -i


Logs and Diagnostics
==========================
35. Show system messages:
            ::> event log show

36. Check recent errors:
            ::> event log show -severity ERROR

37. Run a diagnostic test:
            ::>system health alert show

38. Show detailed node errors:
            ::>node run -node <node_name> sysconfig -a
